+"""SLICE-001: edge-list text -> Graph parser.
+
+Reads the file at ``path`` line by line, skipping blank and ``#`` comment lines. A
+valid line is ``"SRC DST"`` (a directed edge) or a single token (an isolated node); a
+line with three or more whitespace-separated tokens is malformed and raises
+:class:`LoaderError` carrying the offending 1-based line number. The resulting
+:class:`~gx.model.Graph` is fully canonical (sorted nodes, sorted edges, sorted
+per-node adjacency), so every downstream computation is deterministic.
